%I A396924 #10 Jul 14 2026 19:40:37
%S A396924 1,1,1,2,1,5,2,6,7,15,3,60,6,136,154
%N A396924 Number of connected regular integral graphs on n vertices.
%C A396924 A (simple, undirected) graph is called integral if all eigenvalues of its adjacency matrix are integers.
%C A396924 For regular graphs, integrality is equivalent to Laplacian integrality (i.e., all eigenvalues of its Laplacian matrix are integers).
%H A396924 N. Johnston, S. Plosker, and L. M. B. Varona, <a href="https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2607.06336">Enumeration of Laplacian integral and {-1,0,1}-diagonalizable graphs</a>, arXiv:2607.06336 [math.CO], 2026.
%H A396924 L. M. B. Varona, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.21114288">Small {-1,0,1}-Diagonalizable Graphs: A Computational Survey</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%e A396924 For n = 4, the only two connected regular integral graphs are K_4 and C_4, so a(4) = 2.
%Y A396924 Cf. A005177 (number of connected regular graphs).
%Y A396924 Cf. A064731 (number of connected integral graphs).
%Y A396924 Cf. A077027 (number of integral graphs).
%Y A396924 Cf. A363064 (number of connected Laplacian integral graphs).
%Y A396924 Cf. A363065 (number of Laplacian integral graphs).
%K A396924 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A396924 1,4
